###########################################################
#04.Variables

1)Variables come in two flavours: primitive and reference 
2)variables must have a type
3)variables must have a name

Example:
int count;
int: type of variable
count : name of variable

4)Primitive Types
a)boolean and char
  - boolean (JVM specific) true or false
  - char 16 bits 0 to 65536
b) Numeric(all are signed)
  - Integer
   a)byte   8 bits : -128 to 127
   b)short 16 bits : -32768 and 32767
   c)int   32 bits : -2147483648 to 2147483647
   d)Long  64 bits : -huge to huge
c) Floating Point
   - float 32 bits varies
   - double 64 bits varis   #all decimal values are default double
  
5)Variable Name
 Name should not be keyword and not start with special characters
 Should start with variable
###########################################################
#05.Variables and Practical
#Code Start#
		int num1 = 5; //declared and initialized
		int num2 = 4; //declared and initialized
		int result = num1 +num2 ;//declared and expression is initialized
		System.out.println(5+4);
		System.out.println("The addition is:"+num1+num2);
		System.out.println("The addition is:"+ (num1+num2));
		System.out.println(result);
 #Code Finish#
 
 




